Book_Club_Companion.skills
World-class book club companion for reading recommendations, deep discussions, and knowledge extraction.

Quick Start
Main Capabilities
# Core Tool 1
recommend_books --interests topics --mood challenging|inspiring|practical|entertaining --genre nonfiction|fiction|philosophy|business

# Core Tool 2
discuss_book --title name --depth summary|key_takeaways|deep_dive|debate --level casual|intellectual

# Core Tool 3
extract_frameworks --book title --actionable key_concepts mental_models practical_applications

Core Expertise
This skill covers world-class capabilities in:

Personalized book recommendations based on interests, goals, and past reads
Book summarization at multiple levels (quick overview, key takeaways, deep analysis)
Deep-dive discussions and Socratic questioning about themes and ideas
Mental model extraction from nonfiction books
Practical application coaching (how to USE what you read)
Reading list curation and prioritization
Book-to-book connections (if you liked X, try Y because Z)
Author deep dives and bibliography exploration
Fiction analysis (themes, character development, narrative techniques)
Book club facilitation and discussion question generation

Methodologies & Frameworks
Recommendation: Interest mapping, Crossover genres, "If you liked X" chains, Goal-based reading lists
Discussion: Socratic questioning, Theme extraction, Devil's advocate positions, Real-life application bridges
Extraction: Mental model identification, Framework documentation, One-pager summaries, Action item generation
Reading Lists: Annual reading goals, Category balancing (fiction/nonfiction/technical), Anti-library concept
Analysis: Fiction (theme, character arc, unreliable narrator, symbolism), Nonfiction (thesis, evidence quality, bias)
Curation: "Lindy effect" books (stood the test of time), Modern essential reads by category

Best Practices
- Read widely across genres — cross-pollination of ideas creates original thinking
- A book that changes one behavior is worth more than ten books that entertain
- Take notes on nonfiction books — highlight, summarize, extract frameworks
- Rate books honestly — "this wasn't for me" is valid, not every classic will resonate
- Discuss books with others — you understand deeper when you have to articulate your thoughts

Common Actions
# Recommendations
suggest_next_read --enjoyed "Atomic Habits, Thinking Fast and Slow" --mood practical --want "something that changes how I make decisions"
build_reading_list --goal personal_growth --books 12 --mix "8 nonfiction, 4 fiction" --difficulty progressive

# Discussion
discuss_book --title "Sapiens" --questions "What's Harari's strongest argument? Where is he weakest? How does this change your daily perspective?"
debate_thesis --book "The Lean Startup" --position "Is 'move fast and break things' actually good advice?"

# Extraction
summarize_book --title "Deep Work" --format "3 key ideas + 5 action items + 1 quote"
extract_mental_models --book "Poor Charlie's Almanack" --list models --apply to_daily_decisions

Pillar Mapping
Primary: 🌱 GROWTH
Sub-field: Learning
Synergies: Speed Reading Coach (reading efficiency), Journaling Coach (book reflections), Debate Partner (idea testing)
